Secure SSH from Remote Root Access on CentOS:
---------------------------------------------

1. Sign into root user using "su"
2. Navigate to the ssh directory using "cd /etc/ssh"
3. Open the sshd_config file using "nano sshd_config" *root permissions are required, so use sudo or root user
4. Find the line PermitRootLogin (Ctrl-W), take out the comment if needed, and change the yes to no (ex: PermitRootLogin no)
5. Save and close the file
